The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, April 16: The International Monetary Fund said the current global recession was likely to continue for a longer duration and recovery would be sluggish. However, strong counter-cyclical policy action, combined with the restoration of confidence in the financial sector, could improve the prospects for recovery.                             
	 Mumbai, April 16: Jet Airways may close down some of its sales offices in major cities as part of its fresh cost-cutting measure amid reports that around 400 employees may lose jobs in the wake of the turbulence in the aviation industry.                            
	 New Delhi, April 16: Unitech today raised $325 million (about Rs 1,568 crore) through private placements, which will result in the promoters share coming down to 13 per cent in the company.                            
	 Mumbai, April 16: Textile firm Arvind Ltd has rescheduled long-term debt worth Rs 904 crore, thereby increasing the average maturity period of these loans by about two years.                                                                                                                           
